Street dancer Moya David has surpassed 2.8 million followers on TikTok, becoming the most-followed Kenyan on the social platform. Moya is known for his common dance moves and use of the 'Mi amor' song. Taking to Instagram to celebrate the mark, Moya thanked his fans, who have made him go 'from strength to strength'. "I am incredibly proud to reach this amazing milestone. I will keep serving you premium content, just the way you like it," he wrote. Earlier on, Moya said self-employment is the way to go for the youth. "I am a journalist by profession and was among the best radio producers during my time in school," he said. He encouraged his fans to go with what works for them as they wait for God to open doors. "Thank you for your amazing support. I became an influencer here because of your constant engagement with my posts."